data.text:
These pages contain the list of books scanned to create the British Library's Mechanical Curator collection of images. Their purpose is to allow the full list to be browsed or searched for particular words, or to be downloaded to use offline tools such as grep. A more detailed dataset, including author and publisher information, and the original pagenumber and size in pixels of each image, can be downloaded as a zipfile of the British Library's project site on github.

A project to create a thematic and geographical index to the source books (or, more specifically, to those books which have a significant number of useful images in them) is underway at

Commons:British Library/Mechanical Curator collection/Synoptic index.

Currently book titles accounting for about 40% of the images in the collection have at least one entry in the synoptic index, so help to improve it would be very welcome. But please keep an entry on this list, even if you have added exhaustive classifications for it to the synoptic index -- both lists have their uses. Titles that have one entry (at least) in the synoptic index have been marked with a +. The special symbol ₪ (Shekel sign) marked all already edit books with individual motifs, which are also available separately to find at the Category:Images with no book category from the British Library Mechanical Curator collection.
